Appendix B — UX/UI Specification & Screen Inventory (Web + Admin)
Version: v1.0   Date: 2025-12-20
This appendix enumerates all required screens and defines UI/UX checklists for TheNexuStore storefront and admin console.
B1) UX/UI Objectives
PCComponentes-level clarity: fast discovery, strong filters, trust elements, frictionless checkout.
Mobile-first responsiveness (≥60% traffic assumption) with excellent Core Web Vitals.
Consistency: design system components reused across web and admin.
Internationalization-ready (ES first, EN optional).
API-first UX: every screen powered by Commerce Core API (no supplier runtime dependency).

B2) Information Architecture (Site Map)
Home
Categories (Mega-menu) → Category Listing (PLP)
Search Results
Product Detail (PDP)
Cart
Checkout (multi-step)
Order Confirmation
Customer Account: Profile, Addresses, Orders, Order Detail, Invoices, Returns (RMA), Wishlist (optional), GDPR/Consents
Content Pages (CMS): About, Contact, FAQ, Shipping, Returns, Warranty, Privacy, Terms
Admin Console: Dashboard, Orders, Catalog, Imports, Pricing, Promotions, Customers, Returns, Shipping/Tracking, Settings, Logs/Audit

B3) Global Design System (Reusable Components)
Header: logo, mega-menu, search bar, account, cart (count), support link.
Footer: legal links, contact, social, payment badges, shipping partners, newsletter.
Product Card: image, title, brand, key specs (2–3), price, availability badge, add-to-cart.
Price Block: sale price, compare-at (optional), VAT/tax note, financing/badge (phase 2).
Availability Widget: in stock / low stock / out of stock; shipping ETA; warehouse vs supplier indicator (internal only).
Filter Facets: brand, price slider, attributes; mobile drawer version.
Sort Control: relevance, price asc/desc, newest, best sellers.
Pagination / Infinite scroll (choose one; pagination preferred for SEO).
Breadcrumbs and canonical SEO URL handling.
Toasts/Notifications: add-to-cart success, error states.
Empty states: no results, empty cart, no orders.
Skeleton loaders (avoid layout shift).
Forms: inputs, validation, error summary (checkout-critical).
Trust Blocks: warranties, secure payment, delivery/returns policy microcopy.

B4) Screen Specifications — Storefront
B4.1 Home Page
Hero: primary value proposition + main CTA (Shop categories / Best deals).
Top categories tiles (6–10).
Featured deals (based on promotions/coupons).
Best sellers and New arrivals (configurable).
Brand strip (top brands).
Trust section: shipping, returns, warranty, secure payment.
Newsletter / lead capture (optional).
SEO: unique H1, meta, internal links to category pages.
B4.2 Category Listing Page (PLP)
H1 category title + short intro (SEO text, CMS-editable).
Left sidebar filters (desktop) and filter drawer (mobile).
Sort dropdown and results count.
Product grid with consistent cards and quick add-to-cart.
Badges: 'In Stock', 'Fast Shipping', 'On Sale'.
Pagination (SEO-friendly).
No-results handling: show suggestions and clear filters CTA.
Performance: SSR/ISR for first load; cache category results.
B4.3 Search Results
Autosuggest dropdown: products + categories + brands.
Search results page with same filters as PLP, plus 'Did you mean'.
Track search queries for merchandising optimization.
SEO: noindex for some search pages if needed to avoid index bloat.
B4.4 Product Detail Page (PDP)
Above the fold: title, brand, rating (phase 2), image gallery + zoom, price block, availability, shipping ETA, add-to-cart.
Variant selection (if any) and compatibility/notes when applicable.
Key specs highlights (4–6) plus full specs table (normalized attributes).
Downloads: manuals/datasheets (if present).
Related: alternatives, accessories, 'customers also bought'.
Trust microcopy: returns window, warranty, payment safety.
SEO: JSON-LD (Product/Offer), canonical, open graph.
B4.5 Cart
Line items with qty controls and remove.
Price summary: subtotal, shipping estimate (optional), discounts, total.
Coupon field (if enabled).
Cross-sell module (accessories / recommended).
Primary CTA: Proceed to checkout.
Persist cart for guest via session; for logged-in via customer_id.
B4.6 Checkout (Multi-step)
Step 1: Email / login (guest allowed).
Step 2: Shipping address + delivery method selection (ETA/cost).
Step 3: Billing address + invoice data (company, VAT ID).
Step 4: Payment (Redsys/Stripe) + anti-fraud basics.
Step 5: Review and confirm (order summary, terms acceptance).
Error handling: clear field errors + global summary; retry payment safely (idempotent).
Compliance: explicit acceptance of Terms/Privacy; capture consent versions.
B4.7 Order Confirmation
Order number + summary + next steps.
Email confirmation message + invoice availability status.
Tracking placeholder (if not yet shipped).
Account creation prompt for guest (optional).
B4.8 Customer Account
Login/Register + password reset flow.
Profile: name, phone, preferences.
Addresses: add/edit defaults (billing/shipping).
Orders list: status, total, date; filter by status.
Order detail: timeline, items, invoice download, shipment tracking.
Returns (RMA): request flow, status updates.
GDPR: consents and data export/delete request mechanism (phase 2 UI if needed).
B4.9 Content Pages (CMS)
About NEXUS / Store info
Contact (form + phone + email + address)
FAQ / Help Center
Shipping Policy
Returns & Warranty
Privacy Policy
Terms & Conditions
These pages must be editable in WordPress headless, but rendered within the storefront layout.

B5) Screen Specifications — Admin Console (Operations Platform)
B5.1 Admin Dashboard
KPIs: orders today, revenue, conversion (if available), AOV, payment failure rate.
Alerts: import failures, low stock (internal), high refund rate, supplier submission errors.
Quick actions: run import, create coupon, search orders.
B5.2 Orders
Orders list: filters (date, status, payment status), search by order number/email.
Order detail: timeline, payment details, items, fulfillment split (internal vs supplier).
Actions: cancel (before shipment), refund/partial refund, resend emails, add internal notes.
Shipment management: create shipment, set carrier, tracking number, update status.
B5.3 Catalog
Product search and editing: title, descriptions, images ordering.
Category assignment (primary + secondary).
Attribute management: create/edit attributes, define filterable attributes.
Media management (image/datasheet).
Merchandising: featured products, category banners (optional).
B5.4 Imports (Supplier Manager)
Run imports: catalog/stock/prices/images.
Import history: status, duration, counts, errors.
Diff view: new products, delisted products, major price changes.
Retries: re-run failed jobs; view raw snapshot reference.
B5.5 Pricing Rules
CRUD pricing rules by scope: global/category/brand/sku.
Priority resolution and preview calculation (show computed sale price for a SKU).
Floor price alerts (selling below cost protection).
B5.6 Promotions & Coupons
Create coupons (percent/fixed), usage limits, validity dates.
Assign promotions to category/brand (phase 2).
Track coupon usage and revenue impact.
B5.7 Customers
Search customers by email/phone.
View order history, addresses, consent logs.
Support actions: disable account (if fraud), reset password link (safe flow).
B5.8 Returns (RMA)
RMA list: requested/approved/received/refunded.
RMA detail: items, reason, notes, decision.
Refund workflow integration with payment provider; generate customer notifications.
B5.9 Settings & Security
Users & roles (RBAC): admin, ops, marketing, read-only.
Audit log viewer (key actions).
Email templates management (optional if not via provider).
System settings: currency, tax mode, shipping rules, legal versions.
B5.10 Logs & Observability
View recent errors (Sentry deep link).
Webhook events viewer: payment callbacks, processing status.
Job queue viewer: running/failed jobs with retry.

B6) UX States and Edge Cases (Must Be Designed)
Out of stock: disable add-to-cart, show alternatives and notify-me (phase 2).
Price changed between browse and checkout: show clear message; require reconfirmation.
Supplier item disappears: mark SKU inactive; keep order history intact.
Payment failures: allow retry without duplicating orders (idempotency key).
Partial shipments: show multiple shipments and tracking numbers.
Returns window expiry: inform user clearly and provide contact path.
Fraud/abuse prevention: rate limit login/checkout; captcha optional on sensitive endpoints.

B7) Analytics & SEO Requirements
Analytics events (GA4 recommended): view_item, add_to_cart, begin_checkout, add_payment_info, purchase; include SKU and value.
Search analytics: capture query, result count, clicks (for merchandising).
SEO: clean slugs, canonical URLs, XML sitemap (products/categories), robots.txt rules.
Structured data: Product, Offer, BreadcrumbList; OpenGraph/Twitter cards for sharing.
Performance: image optimization, lazy loading, SSR/ISR; avoid CLS with fixed media ratios.

B8) Accessibility & Quality
Keyboard navigation for menus, filters, modals.
ARIA labels for buttons and form fields.
Color contrast compliance; error messages readable.
Form validation that is both field-level and summary-level in checkout.

B9) Mobile App Readiness (No Extra Backend Needed)
All storefront actions must exist as API endpoints; no logic only in UI.
Use consistent DTOs and versioned endpoints for mobile stability.
Webhooks for order/shipment updates if mobile push is added later.

